    • Method Detail

      • makeShape

        protected final void makeShape​(int radius)
        Returns the set of all points in a circle of a specified radius (kind of).

        Checks all points from (0,0) to (radius-1, radius-1). If x^2 + y^2 <= radius^2 it adds that point in each quadrant. This results in a circle with a diameter of 2*radius-1, which means the circle's radius != radius. // <-- fix this //

        Parameters:
        radius - radius of the circle + 0.5
